Clothing , footwear and accoutrements identified gender , status , rank and social class , and thus offered a means of social control . This was probably most apparent in the segregation of seating tiers at public theatres , games and festivals . Magistrates , priesthoods and the military had their own distinctive and privileged forms of dress .
